<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c6ee19a-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2737"><num value="2737">§ 2737.</num><heading> Limitation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other law, tank vessels that have spilled more than 1,000,000 gallons of oil into the marine environment after <date date="1989-03-22">March 22, 1989</date>, are prohibited from operating on the navigable waters of Prince William Sound, Alaska.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c6ee19b-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/380/tV/s5007">Pub. L. 101–380, title V, § 5007</ref>, <date date="1990-08-18">Aug. 18, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/554">104 Stat. 554</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
